reviews:
Cosy small boutique hotel. Modern and clean with a very friendly and caring staff. Highly Recommended.

Only negative is that it is not a very exciting area (nothing really to discover and not very exciting restaurants), but with subway line 1 just one minute from the hotel it is very practical to be anywhere within 20 minutes.

The Piapia Hotel in Paris was a reasonably priced place to stay in Paris. Our five-day visit was very busy and the hotel was a good resting spot away from the touristy areas. The metro and the bus stops were within easy walking distance, the breakfast was abundant and good, staff were helpful and friendly, and there is a little cafe/bar a few doors down that we quite enjoyed. The only thing I could suggest is better lighting, perhaps overhead in addition to the bedside area.

The Room was quiet and nice. With the three of us a bit crowded but ok.Short distance to walk to the Metro station. Breakfast Buffet was good. All was clean and the staff was very friendly. We were happy to stay there.

Superb little hotel, fantastic staff, nice simple breakfast buffet with scrambled eggs and bacon, bread rolls, pastries, cheeses and cured meats. Pricing is OK for Paris. My (budget by choice) room was on the small side but very nice all the same. I'm coming back.

Chose this hotel as close enough to spend a few days travelling to Disney and a few days seeing the sights around Paris. The hotel is close to metro and has a supermarket and several nice eateries local for the nights we arrived back from Disney and needed to eat. La sabonne nearby is lovely.
The hotel is super clean, the rooms were cleaned so well every morning. The rooms are well decorated and bathrooms feel lovely and new. The free water and hot drinks throughout the day was a godsend, getting a coffee in the morning and hot chocolate at night was great touch. We didn’t have breakfast but it looked bustling with a great choice of food.
Our only criticism would be the room. As a family of 5 we booked a family room so expected a suite or interconnecting rooms. We arrived late and were given our room keys only to find a main door with two rooms, one to the left and one to the right, both with a separate door, all seemed fine but turns out the main entrance door didn’t lock - went to reception who came to look but the main door didn’t lock and didn’t have the facility to lock so basically we had two rooms. Not quite what we booked. Not being able to lock the main door meant husband had to sleep with two children and me with another child all because we couldn’t lock the main door. Not what we booked. Be warned if you want to be able to move between rooms as a family this isn’t guaranteed. I’ve never had an interconnecting room like this anywhere in Europe before. We were told the manager would be in touch in the following morning but never heard anything.
Thankfully we still enjoyed our trip and at night we were so shattered and all we wanted was to go to sleep, but it wasn’t the room we booked/expected. Worth noting if you are travelling as a family.

Good hotel located near Nation. Well served by metro. Very confortable, top breakfast, small but confortable room, clean with super maintenance of rooms and structure. Good amenities ( coffee, tea, camomille etc, thoughout the day ).
Wormely suggested. Price in line with service given.

Cute concept. Clean. Great Value. Near the Metro. Well maintained. Reataurant and shops all around. If you’re out touring and need a good sleep, this is where you go. I will recommend to friends and family.

For context, my husband and I stayed here for 3 nights.

Pros about this hotel
-Very clean! The housekeeping staff were amazing and even gently put our suitcases away
-Staff is kind

Cons about this hotel
-This hotel is very east from the city center. Every site was about 30 minute train ride (which are very packed mind you). At times we just opted to walk for that reason
-Rooms are tiny! I mean very tiny! There wasn't much space to put our luggage and we had to get creative. The room size won't be a nuisance to solo travelers, but I would not recommend if you are a couple or if someone in your party is 6 foot ( 1.8 meters) or taller
-Breakfast was pricey for what is offered (basic croissants, orange juice and slices of bread with jam)
-The room was very cold at night and we could not change the temperature

Nice interior and clean (with even a nice smell). Rain shower is amazing and the ring light in the bathroom works perfect for makeup. If we go to Paris again, I would stay here again. Would recommend!

I would gladly recommend the PiaPia to anyone staying in the 20th arondisement in Paris. It is clean and very safe. The staff were very kind and knew English. The room was good sized by European standards and was very comfortable. It was easily within walking distance to the metro which made it a great starting point for seeing the city.

I found this hotel to be 3 star, but it surpassed many 4 star hotels I've been to.
Great hotel, very friendly staff, everywhere clean, small, but cosy room. Several metro and bus stops near the hotel. I will stay here again next time I visit Paris.

- Ideal location in an area called Porte de Vincennes around 15-20 mins from central Paris. - Tube station is within 2 mins walking distance if that.
- Clean, modern and warm with good furnishings and comfortable bed.
- Friendly staff with good tips for travellers - they even provide free refreshments whenever you need.
- Not too expensive room rates for Paris
- Really good amenities- the shower was great although a little on the small side.
- The room overall is small but for sight seeing where you’re not spending much time in the hotel it wasn’t really a problem.

Highly recommended as we didn’t have any complaints!

P.s there’s a great boulangerie across the road called Maison Cailleaud - almond crossiant and pain au chocolat which were really tasty!!

Thank you Piapia :)

Nice, clean room; very friendly staff! We spent two nights in the hotel PiaPia. My husband enjoyed the always available free coffee. The breakfast buffet looked nice although we had decided to go put and have breakfast in one of the Parisian bakeries.

Hotel is cozy, in a good location, and staff is very friendly. Noise from hallway can be heard in the rooms, and space is tight if sofa bed is opened. And when I say tight, it’s TIGHT! No parking available but there’s a parking garage about a 7 minute walk away.

Very good Place Hood Staff Cleaned. But the only problem is Room was so Small. And There was no Bed Table. Next door Guests when use toilet i used to heard noise of their flush in my room. Amd it was a loud.

(+) Clean good hotel located in quite area near to metro line M1, friendly staff in the reception (-) We had just 1 soap for two people for 4 days. Finally we request one more soap for the 5-th day. I understand that it's a crisis time, but I don't think that saving money on hygiene is a good solution. Also we had only 2 times water bottles in the room for period of 5 days.

I want clean and quiet and that's what I got and what is most important to me. So, I can forgive that the room was quite small. The breakfast was great and the staff was helpful and pleasant. Close to M1 Metro line, which is very handy.

The hotel is new renovated. We booked the deluxe room because we need a spacious bed. The room was nice and clean. For our room we have a bathtub, two bathroom sinks and separated toilet.
There's a safe deposit box, coffee machine.
The breakfast was good. As a critique, the height of the tables and the chairs at the breakfast room is too low. So it's not really comfortable to sit.
The location is bit far from the central but there's a metro station 200 m from the hotel, so if you have time to explore and are fit, it should not be a problem.
The staff were nice and friendly. There are coffee machine that can be use freely all day.
Overall it's a really nice hotel.

Very good and clean hotel. Breakfast was very good and free coffee all day and night. Excellent staff and very helpful. Cliose to metro, station and restaurants nearby. Could not have stayed in a netter hotel. Would highly recommend this hotel.

The room was clean and comfortable, the staff was very friendly and helpful. The breakfast was good. The hotel was closely related to public transport facilities making it a good place to make trips to the city.

It’s a very nice place where to stay in paris! The rooms are very nice especially the DELUXE ONE.. the staff are very helpful and nice also!Will stay again when we will had a chance to comeback.. MERCI!

This hotel is perfectly located away from hustle and bustle but next to 2 metro stations minutes walk away to get you quickly to anywhere in Paris. The staff are the nicest people you can meet. Rooms are not big but on a budget a bargain, I went on trip advisor found cheapest rate went to Expedia as member and a discount was applied. This hotel is 50 yards away from a pub with good food and they all speak better English than us Geordies. My only downside was the flight with Vueling airline. We arrived at ORLY for flight to find it cancelled. We expected they would put us in hotel and arrange flight to Newcastle, They left us stranded my wife 74 Yrs old with memory problems and me 71 yrs old today deaf and with heart problem. We had to get to other airport book a hotel book flights with AIRFRANCE for next day. Absolute nightmare. After 10 emails they gave us 148euro. The flight I had to book was 500 euros, Please do not our experience with Vueling put you off. Go with a good airline. We would like to thank people who helped my wife when she fell over. All the French we met especially the young people were fantastic,

The hotel was recently renovated, so everything is in top condition. Air conditioning also works well, which was a big plus, as the summer weather reached 40 degrees. The staff was friendly and welcoming. And the location near the metro station was super handy. I would choose this hotel again.

The Piapia hotel is a decent place but incredibly small, to the point that you can move around in the bathroom (or in the room) without hitting a wall. Breakfast is ok, wifi is good, sound isolation between room is not great.

Overall it’s a decent stay but nothing above average.

The stay in the city of Paris with the family in Pia Pia was excellent. The perfect short distance to the Metro made us explore the city easily. The hotel is stylish, clean and really comfortable for a three-star hotel. We would recommend it for any family stay in Paris.

This hotel is in a perfect location, out of the hustle and bustle but right next to bus stops and metros that take you anywhere you want to go in around 30 mins. The reception staff were always friendly and helpful when we told them our fridge didn’t work (they replaced it!) and got us an extra pillow.
Breakfast was definitely worth the extra small amount we added on booking - a great selection and really fresh.
The bed was super comfy and our room (deluxe) was spacious, with big windows, a tv, and really nice double sink in the bathroom.
I would definitely go back there!

I would highly recommend Hotel Piapia. The staff at reception were always very welcoming and helpful. The hotel was very clean and the bed was so comfortable! The location felt very safe and had great transportation links. Would recommend to friends and family!

Room i got was really to small even by paris standards. Can not put down luggage or even toilet bag in the bathroom. Als decoration feels bit like mercure hotel so not very premium. Bathroom itself is nice but to small to do anything. No waste basket in room so improvements can be made.

Beautifully modern, wonderful decor and absolutely charming. Excellent staff. Clean and spotless throughout. Showers amazing and rooms small but comfortable. Location good - close to the Porte de Vincennes Metro and some good bar/brasseries.

The hotel and the staff were just fabulous! As soon as we arrived, the staff at the front desk were warm and friendly. They very kindly upgraded our room. They were polite, funny and friendly - and this was just on arrival. The hotel itself is modern with a nice ambiance. Staff around the hotel would greet us with morning / bonjour and were smiling - all were very genuine. We had forgotten some things in the hotel and they have very kindly offered to post these goods to us - the communication is constant. We were so happy with our stay and will definitely go back! Thank you to all

Very nice, cozy, clean hotel in a pleasant district. Quiet street, area is calm, a bit away from the centre, but very well connected and easy to move around.
The simplest room is rather small (9m2) but it's ok for a few days stay for the offered price and there's working area downstairs.
On my second stay I got a free upgrade to a bigger room and it was very pleasant.

I strongly recommend hotel Piapia and its nice staff.
It is a quiet place with high quality sleeping accommodation.
The only black spot is the absence of parking lot, but this is usual in Paris.
Good deal

I really enjoyed my stay at PiaPia. It was very clean, brilliant decor, the staff were so professional and free tea/coffee on tap. The location was fine I didn’t have much time to explore the immediate area so I give it 3 just because I travelled 30 minutes to most places but everything else totally fab. The only downside is that the rooms are not totally soundproof and I could hear movement plus some construction works going on next door. That being said I would definitely stay here and certainly at another hotel by the same company. Brilliant!

Stay here for 9 nights. Got 2 super receptionist both are woman who wear glasses. Both perform top class. They treat us like we stay at 5 star hotel. The first receptionist one who were taller was very helpful and even give us a map to help us navigate around city. Second receptionist was super warm and smile for us everyday. I even remember how she stand and smile and waited for us to depart out of the hotel during our last day in Paris. Because of this hotel, sometimes i feel Parisian actually was more polite than Japanese. For 140usd++/night in Paris, you have quite lot of hotels selection, but if you want to stay in quote neighborhood, got lot of cheap food, close to 2 main line train, top class receptionist and staff, then hotel Comete was the best. Definitely stay here again for the next roland garros or rolex paris master.

Pros:
-Lot of cheap food (darjeling, chinese food etc)
-got carefour and lot of boulagerie
-both of your receptionist (women who wear glasses) are all perform like 5 star hotel!!!
-got 2 main line train (porte de vincennes can take you to louvre etc) and (mareichers can take you directly to roland garros and eiffel tower via iena)
-bonus cookies was amazing
-very good smell inside hotel
-super clean
-modern boutique hotel

Minus:
-honestly i dont know

We had a nice stay at this charming and nicely decorated hotel. We loved the vintage vibe!
The lady at the reception was very friendly and welcoming. The room was good; very tidy and clean. Only the airco didn’t work properly.
Breakfast buffet was perfect!
Metro / bus stops to all different areas in Paris are only a short walk away. Ideal for a weekend trip to Paris!

Couldn't complain about anything really except that although advertised the air conditioning was turned off. Clean, comfortable and spacious room. Excellent breakfast for a small Parisien hotel. Would stay again.

Fantastic hotel, easy to get to on the metro if a little far out of the centre. Wooden floors mean you can hear people walking about. Great staff and good service. Breakfast was nice and simple but plenty of choice.

Nicely decorated small hotel. Close to metro. Clean modern room. Good beds. Area itself is not bad still paris feeling

Downside: coffee machine in room broken, no real emergency exit (only one staircase going down), wifi slow

Great location for the Metro meant that whilst not near any tourist attractions. You could get to all of them within 25-50 mins depending on where you going.

Also easy to get to & from Gare Du Nord (28 mins) by Metro Good choice at breakfast, comfortable beds, our superior room was a good size. I had to remind staff we were supposed to have macaroons. Which we promptly received with a smile.

Only ‘moan’ is there was no full length mirror. Just the mirror in the bathroom above the sink. When out & about in a stylish city like Paris. It’s nice to check on your appearance before heading out on the town! Lol

Last but by no means least, the staff were hospitable, attentive and friendly. Merci beaucoup to the young man who was on breakfast duties. Also the staff who dealt with my special requests for the welcome notes to be left in our rooms :-)

Overall would recommend and definitely stay again. Although as I like to explore and experience new things. If like with this booking (Secret Escapes) a good deal is available. I may try somewhere else when next in Paris.

I booked this hotel stay and was looking forward to it given the pictures and the reviews.
Good-the hotel looked like the pictures and was in a good location, breakfast was good and the rooms were nice
Bad- we booked superior rooms and when we got to the hotel they told us that we were in classic rooms- when I showed the staff our booking they said that they had changed the names of the rooms since we booked, even though the website still has superior rooms on. This was not a good start.
2 days before we arrived I called to ensure we had twin rooms and were told that was no problem (the website also says this is fine if in a superior room). When we arrived we were told this was not possible and that there was no record of this on our booking. When I showed the record of the call on my phone they still insisted nothing could be done even though they had previously said this was fine.
The website also says you get water and macaroons in the room which we never saw as the hotel said they had run out.

Overall this was a very disappointing stay and I would not recommend given the hotel did nothing to try and make amends. This meant we had to have a 12 year old child sleeping in a room alone and meant someone had to stay with him until he fell asleep and someone had to come early in the morning to ensure he was not scared.
This does not make for a relaxing holiday.

Well designed room, comfortable, quiet and clean. Very quiet location, near a Tube stop, a bit far from the city centre, in a quiet quarter. Staff very polite and friendly, stunning air conditioning in the middle of the last heat weather episode.

This hotel is something of a find. The deluxe room we had was large with an enormous double (and extremely comfortable) bed. It was also quiet (on the fifth of six floors). The bathroom catered for two at once and the safe was big enough to take all of our valuables as well as a large laptop. Our son had his own single room which, although smaller than ours, had a double bed big enough to generously accommodate his lanky frame. He was particularly pleased with the free wifi which he deemed to be appropriately fast. We went during the recent heatwave and were grateful for the quiet but efficient air-conditioning. Housekeeping was exceptional (towels and bedding were immaculate) as was front of house. There were a few changes of staff at the front desk during our stay, but thankfully they all spoke excellent English (my schoolboy French would only have confused them otherwise). One lady - I'm ashamed to say I never asked her name, but she said that she was originally from Romania - took the time to recommend a few supermarkets (wine and croissants!) and restaurants in the area. In fact the location - although a little out of town - was well served with eateries, and, if you like Italian food, we recommend Il Santo on the Avenue du Dr Arnold Netter just across the main road. On the subject of location - the Metro station is a few minutes walk from the hotel and it's at the end of Line 1 so it'll take you quickly to pretty much anywhere you might want to visit as a tourist. We found the RATP smartphone app invaluable, and made it from Gare du Nord to the hotel in about thirty minutes with only one change of line. Hotel Comete is highly recommended and when we revisit Paris (soon!) we do not intend to stay anywhere else.

Nice, clean and comfortable modern hotel with lovely big bathrooms. Staff friendly and helpful. Location is just round the corner from the metro line 1,which means you can get around Paris very easily though the hotel is quite far out of the centre. Breakfast was ok and you could get free water and fruit at any time, though sometimes there was no fruit. My only criticism is there is no mirror in the bedroom! Very difficult to dry your hair etc with no mirror. I don’t think you would be disappointed with this hotel.

This place is awesome!! It's a small quiet hotel. The staff is extremely nice and their breakfast in the morning is great. One of the biggest things for me when I travel is that they have good air conditioning and this place has an amazing air system. The location is right next to the metro which takes you everywhere. loved it will come back

Good place to stay for few days but it’s a little bit far away from the Eiffel Tower 25-30 minutes drive it’s in a quiet location but I thought the room was a little bit on the small side and the bathroom has a pocket door:)

I've been at the Hotel Comete on holiday with my daughter, end of April. We spent there five days and I must say I really liked my staying. The hotel is clean (rooms, bathroom, breakfast room...). Our room was small but cosy and comfortable: they cleaned it every day, leaving a bottle of water for every guest. In the room there was also the espresso machine Nescafè if you want to enjoy Italian coffee. The bathroom was small (but who cares? You just need the hotel for the night!) but fully equipped. No noisy people, no traffic noise, but a still and quiet place. Breakfast is great: plenty of different kinds of food and beverages, clerks of the hotel very friendly and helpful.
The hotel is near the underground station which takes you everywhere in minutes but if you want to walk it's not far from centre. There is also a wide choice of restaurants nearby, as well as a supermarket.
Definitely, I had a gret holiday!

A small and clean Hotel. the Rooms are not very large too, but clean and the bathroom has a fantastic schower. Good Relaxing shower after a Long walk through Paris.
The room for breakfast is small too and the tables and chairs are very low. Interessting to sit there. But the buffet is very fine. I enjoyed to eat there.

Enjoyed my stay here at Hotel Comete. Very very clean room. Comfortable bed. A/C worked great. Love the shower! This hotel is a bit from the “major sites” but for that exchange you get a quiet safe surrounding. UBer rides to any major site about $15-20 USD; if your traveling solo or would rather save a few Euros there is a metro spot at the end of the street. Breakfast is nice - great coffee machine. Good selection of cheeses, sliced meat, breads, scrambled eggs, bacon, croissants, neat machine for making poached eggs and fresh squeezed orange juice. Day staff was very friendly- especially Erna who was very accommodating and helpful - Thanks Erna!!

My friend and I got a great deal for this hotel via secret escapes and I cannot fault any part of it. It’s a very small boutique hotel and every member of staff was friendly and helpful. It was stylish, very clean, and the breakfast was delicious. Honestly the best scrambled eggs I think I’ve ever had - I need to know the secret!!

Thank you for a wonderful stay and I’d definitely stay here again and recommend to others.

This hotel is a small boutique type hotel. It’s very new inside, spotlessly clean. Good self service breakfast and a good location to access central Paris on the adjacent Metro Line. We thought the price was very reasonable for such a good base to explore Paris.

We travelled as a family of 5. After an exhausting but highly enjoyable 3 days in Disneyland we commuted up to this boutique hotel. Check in at 2pm but our rooms were available on arrival after mid day. Fabulous reception staff who welcomed us by name as they were expecting us! 2 rooms were adjacent and although separate were on a secluded corridor with one door so when locked opened up our stay into a fantastic suite. Only 4 rooms per floor (6) so each floor had similar suites throughout. The beds were fabulous, clean linen and soft pillows and quilts. Air con, water, fridge, Nespresso machine, hairdrier (excellent), toiletries, bath in one room and shower in other. Large plasma tv in each room, free WiFi and proper single bed added for extra child. Fresh towels, water and housekeeping each day. Trouser press and iron and irojing board. Breakfast fresh and substantial. 10 min walk to tour eiffel line and course de vincennes metro at top of street (1min). Lots of restaurants, supermarkets, take aways within a few minutes. Staff very friendly with great English. Bar on site. Unfortunately we couldn't stay longer. Jam packed schedule for us from.morning until nite. Kids wanting to go home at every opportunity ie hotel comete as they loved it. All in all fabulous and I would hope to return and I am not easily pleased lol!!!

I am so glad I found this hotel. It is honestly one of the best hotels I've stayed in regardless of size. Lovely decor. Clean and modern decor. All the little touches of a much higher star hotel i.e. slippers, bottle of water refreshed everyday.

The staff were friendly and helpful but they weren't too intense which I've found with some smaller hotels. The hotel entrance is 24/7 and reception is always manned. The breakfast is amazing and the cappuccino even though it's from a machine is incredible. I would go back here or recommend to friends in a heartbeat.

The hotel is situated on the edge of zone 1 but right on the metro for porte de Vincennes, meaning it took us 15 mins into central Paris, 40 to the airport and about the same to Disneyland. It was perfect for us.

All for a great price? If you're stuck on deciding - go!

My partner and I stayed at Hotel Comete for a weekend break in October. Our room was a reasonable size for a weekend break and the finish was stylish and practical. At breakfast there was a lot of choice and despite being late comers the food buffet had been replenished and was fresh. The staff were very welcoming and informative. The area surrounding the hotel has a secondary school and feels safer to walk around. Would definitely return to stay at Hotel Comete.

I stayed for 3 nights to do a tourism “blitz” on Paris and, as has been noted by others, although it is not in a central district, it’s proximity to the Metro makes it an ideal, and very good value, base.

My room was clean and quiet, the bathroom, with an excellent shower, was very modern and well equipped.

Again as been noted by others, the staff go out of their way to be pleasant and helpful. The breakfast is extremely good and varied and the nearby streets offer a wide selection of different restaurants.

A really ideal base

This is a real gem. Although it isn't in the center of Paris, it is a block from the subway that will get you there in 17 minutes. It's in a quiet neighborhood -- by Paris standards -- with plenty of restaurants nearby. The rooms are large -- by Paris standards. Best of all is the staff. They actually care whether you enjoy your stay in their hotel and in Paris. There is no question that I'd stay here again.

I have been very comfortable in Comete Hotel. Very nice and tidy rooms. And the staff very helpful. My daughter and me needed a break and we could not choose better. Amazing the silence and respect to intimacy. Breakfast: seemed home made. Thanks for making us happy.

The staff is very friendly and helpful. Although the elevator broke down two times during my eight day stay, the location is very convenient and accessible to the Metro. I would recommend this hotel to other people staying in Paris.

It’s a rare thing to find such a low-cost hotel in Paris. Such amazing and spacious rooms. Clean and tidy. Staff was super helpful and welcoming, and helped me a lot organizing a surprise for my bf. They gave us a better room, because of the occasion we had. Strongly recommending!

We stayed three nights. Staff was courteous and helpful. The rooms on both occasions were clean, comfortable, quiet and had good bathrooms. The breakfasts were great. Most of all we took advantage of the hotel's proximity to the metro which made our Paris visit so easy! We will come back to this hotel when we return to Paris. Highly recommended.

Stayed for 2 nights and the hotel and staff were lovely!
The room was lovely comfy bed and good amenities such as a good hairdryer, ness press machine and fridge. The bathroom was gorgeous such a nice shower.
The hotel itself is a fair distance from the airport a taxi cost about €40. However it is about a 5 min walk from The metro and from that you can get anywhere. I got a 2 day ticket for zones 1-3 but would only need a zone 1 if I returned as all major sights are in zone 1 as well as the hotel. Little tip is to download the Paris metro map app on to your phone great for getting around and knowing which line and what direction of metro you need to get on. Our 2 day pass was around €20 each so a single zone ticket would be less.
The breakfast at the hotel was lovely cannot fault however I’d say get there early as some things can run out other than that the breakfast is lovely lots of choice and the dining area is suberbly decorated.
The area around the hotel is nice lots of restaurants I went to a sushi restaurant and it was relatively cheap €20 for all you can eat. A couple of supermarkets for snacks and drinks and trams close by.
Overall the stay was amazing would completely return again!

I was really impressed with this hotel. The staff went out of their way to be helpful. The room was extremely comfortable and the breakfast was great. I highly recommend the hotel and will hopefully stay there again in the future.

We only stayed one night but honestly wish we spent more time here. The hotel is conveniently located a block away from the metro. The woman at the front desk was so nice and showed us all the tourist attractions on a map with restaurant recommendations. She went above and beyond to make sure we felt comfortable. We’d definitely go back here and recommend others to go as well!

This hotel is off the center of Pariss, but close enough to take Metro 1 toward La Defense and you are getting to all the Paris attractions. Also, there is a nearby term that can take you to other areas of town. The staff is very nice and helpful, especially Angelique that assist us by giving us instructions on how to get around and find the local scene. The area is very ethnic and on Saturday there is a local market.

We have been to Paris several times, at different hotels over the years. While we did not encounter any rudeness in our previous visit, we can’t remember a more obliging staff than those I encountered at Hotel Comete. We arrived few hours prior to check-in time and when we explained to Tamar that we needed to attend a family function, she was able to request a speedy room clean up. We were able to access to our room two hours prior to the standard check-in time. Later, Angelique took time out to explain the touristy spots that were easy access from the hotel on the metro line 1 (the metro line closest to the hotel).
Beside the fabulously friendly staff, not just Tamar and Angelique, but everyone else we dealt with, the hotel has a boulangerie/patisserie a stone throw away (around 300 m away). We spend many happy mornings exploring its croissants and patisseries offerings. The super market Franprix is also conveniently close to create a pick-nick basket of your liking without breaking the bank.
We also like our room, which is of decent size for two persons. Actually, we just came back from Kyoto so the room was quite large compared to what we were used to in Japan.
The only minus, and this is very personal, was the daily free water bottles we received from the hotel. We would have preferred that the hotel provides a refill fountain for our water bottles and thus, decreases the amount of throw away plastic.
Overall, we love this hotel.

We stayed at Comete for our short break in Paris as a family of four and we could not have made a better choice. Friendly and helpful staff, great attention to details, yummy breakfast, convenient location close to the metro station - great value for money.

We enjoyed our recent stay at the Hotel Comete. The location was was very close to the Porte de Vincennes Metro Station on Line 1 - which made getting to all the major tourist spots very easy! The staff were welcoming and friendly. We had a room for 3 people and had a good amount of space. The bathroom area was quite large with 2 sinks a nice shower. The only thing we would change about the room is that we wish there was a full-length mirror. Every day the hotel provided free bottles of water in our room, which was a nice touch!

Our stay at Hotel Comete Paris was perfect. Good location with easy access to the public transport, nicely decorated interior, good breakfast and very friendly and professional staff. Highly recommended

We spent a week in Paris and stayed at the Hotel Comete. The rooms were very nice and the breakfast was so delicious! The staff were particularly helpful and attentive. The location is good--near a Metro station. I highly recommend this hotel!!

This was my third stay at the Hotel Comete, and it's just as good as ever, if not better. Having stayed in many hotels over the years, I can say that this is one of my two favourites (it's a close call as to which is best) and easily the best value hotel in a major city. Why? Firstly, the staff go out of their way to make sure everything about your stay is perfect. Secondly, the rooms which, while compact, are tastefully furnished, spotlessly clean and equipped with everything you might need, including a safe. Third, the modern bathrooms with rain shower. Fourth, added bonuses such as the espresso machines in every room, free bottles of water, and fresh macaroons on the first night. Fifth, the excellent breakfast with fresh croissants, breads, beautiful scrambled eggs, cheeses, fruit, apple tart, yoghurts, and more. Sixth, the location, in a nice area, just a minute from the metro line 1 and tram lines 3. And finally, the room rates which represent amazing value for money. Superb!

Was worried on arrival about location but it is a very well appointed hotel and only 200 meters walk from the main line to central Paris and main sights. We travelled using the underground to get around and found it hassle free for a family of 5. Enjoyable breakfast and the lovely lady attending the area was more than helpful in offering gluten free alternatives for our daughter. Great stay, thankyou.

Excellent orange juice and breakfast. Yogurt, scrambled eggs, hams, cheese are really good.
Bathroom shower needs better design, water splash out a lot.
Very convenient to local cell phone stores and markets.
2 blocks to subway station short walking distance. Close after 11pm. 30 mins subway to Champ Elysées. It’s a direct line, no need to transfer. Daily pass €3 unlimited within Paris center.
The manager and the girls are really nice. Other guys not so much.
In room WiFi weak.
Safe neighborhood quiet street.
I would stay there again and recommend this hotel to anyone.

We booked this hotel based on TripAdvisor recommendations and the fact that it had parking available. The parking was a bit deceiving, even though they do have 4 spots in a garage nearby, the daily fee of €25 wasn't mentioned anywhere, so be aware of that when you're travelling by car. The rooms were clean and modern, albeit a bit small. The breakfast buffet was very good, and there were free bottles of water available 24h, handy for when you're going out for a day in the city. The hotel is situated at the outside of the city, but the yellow metro line stop is right around the corner and takes you to the heart of the city in 20min.

Overall very pleased here, will bookmark it for a future Paris trip.

Our room was clean, comfortable and the staff was friendly. Located in a quiet zone (not much touristy) but i think is safe and close to metro by walk. The room has a nespresso machine, great beds, modern bathroom, well decorated and big windows. Please try the breakfast was plenty of options and delicious!

OK, so I booked this place for just one night and the amenities in the place were just fine. The room was clean and the service was good. The coffee machine though was complicated. I'd have really preferred a simple kettle. The macaroons on the bed was a nice touch though....
Breakfast was delicious. And the coffee there was great
The only problem I had was the neighbourhood. I had chosen this place because it was right in the middle of my trajectory in terms of where I was coming from and where I wanted to go, however I didn't realise that it was close to a public square where they chose to have a demonstration. The metro to the stations were disrupted and I took a taxi to be on the safer side. A little warning would've been nice...
Apart from that really nice place to stay

This is a lovely little hotel. The staff are friendly, rooms are a good size, well decorated and comfortable. It's in a good location, not right in the centre so it's quiet but is only a minutes walk to the metro and you can get into the main tourist area within 15 minutes. The only thing I could fault is that there wasn't much variety of drinks behind the bar, but that made no impact on our stay whatsoever. Breakfast was also delicious and had loads of variety! Would definitely stay here again.

it is probably one of the coziest hotels i've stayed in. it was clean, nicely decorated. the patio was like sitting on the porch of you own home , with two line on which huge light bulbs hanging above you. the staff were great . breakfast was minimal however enough to leave you very satisfied. it is also very conveniently located close to the metro. i would recommend this hotel for couples on a budget.

I have certain criteria when selecting an hotel. Must have a minimum 4.0 from TripAdvisor, be close to transport links and, if possible of the main road. Hotel Comete meets all of them.

It is 100m from metro line 1, tram line 3 and bus stops. It is a 10 minute walk to Place de la Nation station which gives more metro lines to choose from. The hotel will look after your bags if you arrive early so take the train from the airport to Chatelet and take metro 1.

The hotel staff are helpful and speak good English. The room was spotless with daily maid service. Small bottles of water were provided free of charge and the room had a Nespresso machine with free capsules. Safe, TV and aircon also in the room.

There is a supermarket a couple of streets away and bars and restaurants nearby.

Would I stay there again? Absolutely.

Great en cosy place and yet very suitable dor business and leisure alike. Interior inspiratie is the sixties. Very tastfull. Breakfast excellent. And service very correct and friendly. Relaxed place. Clean and for Paris city not too small rooms either.

I enjoyed my stay in Comète Hotel. I had a Warm welcome including typical French delicacies and water. The room was Clean, nicely decorated and it included a Nespress. The neighborhood is quiet but close to public transport and easily accessible from périphérique.

Stayed there from 6/24 to 6/27. Clean room, well insulated wall (better than US chain hotels such as HI, Hilton, etc.) Helpful staff. Visited 3 restaurants in the area to soak in the local atmosphere. Metro line1 nearby. Only downside is the room size, but it's still decent for Paris. Highly recommended.

very nice hotel, great breakfast, quick arrive to city center with metro line 1 (metro station 2 min walk), decoration and design in the bathroom is very classy!
the receptionist at nights not very nice... started shouting at us in French beacuse we wanted to host friends in our room...

Very good place. Also I had booked via booking,com lowest rate non refundable. I had to change the date. Booking,com replied "NO, Not possible". After contacting the hotel directly they have changed the date without extra cost. 5 star service!!!

Hotel had incredible rooms. Bathrooms were nicely appointed, and breakfast was great. The immediate area surrounding the hotel is a little plain, but only a few blocks away are some good restaurants and shopping. Water pressure was great, elevator was big enough, and front desk staff was very helpful!!!

Almost brand new 3 star elegant hotel in east of Paris. 300mtr. from metro. Room (Deluxe Room) very nicely decorated (but not over designed) with separate bath room anex toilet. Everything in room was rather new so that was nice. Room cleaning was accurate. Most positive thing however I found was the breakfast witch was exellent for a 3 star hotel and only 13 euro. Didn't expierence any inconvience of other guest rooms or outside stuff like noise. Personal settings possible for airco/heater, room did still smell a little like new. Nice flat screen tv with lots of HD channels. Neighbourhood rather calm (although some schools at nearby). Staff rather friendly and professional. So in my opinean a very good Hotel.

Excellent value! Modern, clean and very quiet.
Hotel staff very friendly and helpfull and the hotel is really close to the tube.
This will be my hotel for all my business travel in Paris.
I highly recommand this hotel.

The best hotel in every thing, comfortable, clean, quiet, free wifi, close to all means of public transportation and the best staff i had ever met.
This will be of course my destination every time i go to paris.

Brilliant hotel close to the metro line.
The hotel was very clean and very relaxing.
The hotel Staff are very friendly and helpful and speak good languages.
Breakfast was good.
Room was clean and well presented.
Only bad point was there was not a good selection of wines.

This is a newly renovated hotel where we stayed for three nights and had a very positive experience. The room and shower were nice and clean; the staff is friendly and accommodating. We didn't eat any meals in the hotel so no comments food-wise; the neighbourhood is not anything spectacular, but the hotel location is very accessible via Metro line 1 to/from Central Paris. We will stay in this hotel again on our next visit to Paris around this time of the year and recommend it to everyone who wishes to opt for a three star hotel with a very good quality of service.

The Hotel is clean. The staff is friendly. The styling is done properly and was well executed. Everything you want to have for a business trip is there. Very clean room, good bed, super shower, good TV, COFFEE MACHINE, free bottle of water, AND SLIPPERS.

If you need a clean good nice comfortable hotel, go here!

I stayed with my family for 3 days & 2 nights. The place was lovely with very nice & accomodating staff. I loved the several choices of food during breakfast. The place is near metro train stations. I will definitely recommend to friends.

I have already reviewed this totally renovated hotel situated conveniently on the number 1 line of the metro system (the line that takes you to all the must-see places like the Louvre, the Champs-Elysées and the Arc de Triomphe). In a side street off of a main avenue, the rooms are very quiet, especially on the courtyard side that overlooks a school playground. The rooms are big by Parisian standards, nice queen-sized bed, big bathroom with roomy shower. The staff is courteous and helpful in every way, someone is at the front desk 24/7 so you can check-in at any time. I cannot say enough good things about it, I now stay there every time I visit Paris. Breakfast is a bit pricey but very good with lots of variety so don't pass it by just based on the cost.

We stayed here for 5 nights and loved it. We were traveling with our infant son and the hotel was very accommodating. They made sure to have a baby cot set up for us and a baby chair every time we came down to breakfast. It is super close to a metro stop so it is easy to get anywhere you want to go in the city. We also really enjoyed walking around the neighborhood. I thought the room was a good size compared to other Paris hotels I've been in. The only downside I would have is that the wifi could be spotty in our room but it was free so I can't complain much!

We found this nice hotel online.
It's well located near metro stop so it's very easy to visit the city.
Staff is very friendly and helpful and the room are nice, clean and comfy.
We will stay there again when we visit Paris!

Quite simply - I loved this little hotel. It looks great, fab interior design. The rooms are lovely, not too small with everything you need. The bed is one of the comfiest I've ever slept in, I'm normally a bad sleeper but slept like a baby in their beds. We did have breakfast, it does seem is a bit steep in price, but there is loads of choice. By the time we finished breakfast we weren't hungry again until the evening. So it did save money in the long run.
The hotel is on the Metro 1 line (get off at Porte de Vincennes). When you come up from the Metro, look for L'Europe bar / café lit up in red in the square, the hotel is down the little street next to it.

This was a great little place to stay and fairly quiet. The hotel owner sent a survey in advance to address any special requirements we had. We did request early check-in for around 9am which we didn't think would even be possible but we decided to indicate it on the survey anyway. To our surprise and delight, a room was made available for us even at such an early hour. Also, instead of housekeeping knocking on our door, they actually phoned the room! That was a pleasant difference from other hotels, and much appreciated.

The good:
Room was very nice, modern, and clean
Staff were very helpful

The bad:
Hotel was not on a good tram line so slightly out from where we wanted to be and longer travel
When checking out they tried to charge us extra for buying drinks however this was incorrect. We never got charged.

Overall was a very nice stay, toilets very modern and hotel room immaculate

Nice design hotel with excellent location which bring you to the city center by subway conveniently. The front desk service is very heart warming and able to provide any help for your trip in Paris. Thanks and will be coming again!

Had a wonderful stay at this boutique hotel. Found a really good deal online and was not disappointed. Easily accessed by the metro, fabulous breakfast and lovely staff. Rooms are small but perfectly formed, very comfy bed. Highly recommended!

The hotel is nicely decorated, very clean, has enough space for us and iit's close to the metro. Their members of staff are very nice especially the italian lady at the morning breakfast. She is very friendly and accommodating. I highly recommend this hotel.

I booked my stay a while ago and discovered that I had made an error with the dates. The hotel was very accommodating and made the changes for me with no problems.

It was really easy to get to from Gare Lyon- only three stops on the number 1 line. One of my friends complained that I was "far out"; I didn't find this at all! The connections and ease to move around Paris from here was perfect for me.

The room that I had was on the third floor- everything was in good condition; very clean and seemed brand new. Free bottled water is provided and was replaced daily; along with a little mini bar fridge with soft drinks. There's a lovely coffee machine in the wardrobe to make coffee or tea- and this was refilled every day. The bathroom is a good size and I loved the shower and toiletries provided :-) In the bathroom there is a fixed hair drier- which had enough power and did not cut out every five seconds.

I would definitely stay here again!
